The answer is 11760 ways to arrange 9 heads and 6 tails (where the number of heads can never be more than 5 units greater than the number of tails) = the case where heads and tails are equal in 15 tosses plus the case where heads is 1 more than tails 14 heads 10 tails + the case where heads is 1 more than tails 13 heads 9 tails + the case where heads is 2 more than tails 12 heads 10 tails + the case where heads is 2 more than tails 11 heads 8 tails + the case where heads is 3 more than tails 10 heads 9 tails

